description:
MenuItem component uses expect_context() which panics if used outside Menu component.

File: src/components/menu/component.rs:218
Severity: Medium
Type: Stability

Current code:
let MenuManager { manual, selected } = MenuManager::expect_context();

This causes panic with unclear error message when MenuItem is used incorrectly.

Recommended fix: Add better error message
let manager = use_context::<MenuManager>()
    .expect("MenuItem must be used within a Menu component");

ClassAttributes uses unreachable!() macro which could panic if internal state management has bugs.

File: src/utils/class_attribute.rs:136,165
Severity: Low
Type: Stability

While logically unreachable in normal execution, unreachable!() in production code can cause panics.

Current code:
} else {
    unreachable!()
}

Recommended fix:
} else {
    leptos::logging::error!("ClassAttributes: unexpected state in rebuild");
    state  // Return existing state rather than panicking
}

This provides defensive programming without sacrificing correctness.
